  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activity 08: Kenya National Committee Memorialization Training</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As part of adopting to the current programming challenges raised by COVID-19, the Africa Programs Office (APO) developed an alternative plan to conduct the KENYA National Committee Memorialization Training virtually while ensuring that the same quality and effectiveness as envisioned during project development prevails. The 5-week KNC Memorialization Training targeted participants from four selected electoral violence hotspots of Mombasa, Nairobi, Kisumu and Uasin Gishu. Under the theme of &#x201C;Prevention of Identity-based Violence in the Great Lakes Region&#x201D;, the training components reflected a combination of Theory, Research, Documentation, Dissemination, and Archiving, capturing the trajectory of electoral violence covering the period of 2007 &#x2013; 2017.</narrative>
  </description>
